The paper deals with the problem of estimating the state of a stochastic process using a limited number of sensors with nonlinear measurements. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including control systems (cs.SY), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on developing an algorithm with linear time complexity and good approximation guarantees suggests that it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these areas.
